Antidu Senarathne aka Ratta aka aka aka there was a press conference at Galle Face yesterday.

There that person is opposing Ranil Wickramasinghe's appointment as Prime Minister.

And Ratta says that instead she presented seven suggestions to change the system.

I didn't read those seven suggestions.

The constitutional changes that weaken the state of the country like implementing those 19 in the Ova, the changes made by the United Nations instead of a country.

Grow the country, make local things, and win the world with our fish, the popular things that are not practical.

It would be nice if we can change a system by doing those things..

But what Ratta doesn't know is that a system is not something that can be changed forcefully or inside.

Y'all call "system" the practical and cultural system that some country, society run.

A system is something that is built among the people of a society and is unique to that society.

It can't be changed from outside or inside.

If we can bring a system in another country and keep it in another country, every country in the world would be England and Switzerland.

But it practically can't be done.

That's why there is another system in England, another system in Africa, and a different system in India.

System is something that is naturally built by the practices, cultures, biological factors of people in those countries.

The system can never be changed, the system evolves. It happens with time.

"System Change" is beautiful as a lesson of political war.

But can't "change the system" With time, the system becomes evolved.

We won't be surprised that the rattas who make YouTube comedy videos don't have knowledge about how they build manners and build society.

But Youtubers have also caught the "Wrong Generation" who mourns that their elder generation sent actors, players to parliament.

Instead of the actors and actresses who were entertaining on TV then, the YouTubeers who are entertaining through popular phones have become public representatives.

Ratta chooses the new generation to change the system instead of the paba who chose the elderly generation, chooses motivation father, Duleka Marapana.

Now what I'm saying is very clear, isn't it?

The system will not change. System can't be changed either. The system is just getting evolved.

Why don't I support the struggle?

Many people ask why young people like me and some political activists are not supporting the anti-government wave.

This is a time where even artists, singers like who worked closely to the government are taking anti-government battles to stay in the field and not to be rejected anymore in social media.

The wave is hitting so hard

No matter how strong the wave is, I have a habit of not getting caught by the popular wave from the past. I need to explain to my generation why I don't support the struggle because of the habit of going against the wave and the full picture I see of the struggle.

I know that the majority are not ready and are not capable to understand this right now. But I consider it my duty to record it somewhere.

Since 1977, the economy of this country has been running on debt.

According to the economic cycle, we should produce what we should consume.

We as a nation did not try to increase production of history. But our consumption is getting more complicated day by day.

Products here I mean goods and service we can earn dollars by exporting and goods and services we consume.

A country should spend, consume the volume that it can afford, manufacture.

We made a billion dollars in the past, consumed five billion dollars.

This scarcity was solved by taking credit.

While this consumer pattern is maintained, there comes a day when pre-debt is paid off.

Crisis arises due to having to pay off debt with less dollars, several times more than that day.

When such times came in the past, past rulers found dollars for consumption by selling national resources.

The previous Yahapalana government took $13 billion ISB loans, sold Hambantota port and gave people food and drinks.

Didn't start projects to make money back with that money. We are a nation that imports $500 million worth of mineral oil. Our import costs are very high.

So past palms even sold ports and searched for money to bring oil and gas.

I don't support these struggles because I reject that consumer pattern that sells or makes the country's resources.

Sirimao Prime Minister was the one who tried to start a production process in the country to some extent. That day also there was polling and shortage of goods in the country like this.

Our elderly generation sent Sirimao home Jay. R is given power of five out of six. The production process stopped with it too.

J. The era of R borrowing and feeding has begun. The country's debt increased by a way.

Today we have come to a crucial junction in the eco-pattern we have run for a long time.

The country's economic crisis has exploded in this season where Gotabhaya Rajapaksha is holding the presidency.

It's just like Anura Kumara said, Gotabhaya is holding the presidency when the crisis is exploding.

It should be said that the Corona epidemic and the Easter attacks should hurry up this crisis after a few years.

Because Gotabhaya Rajapaksha is not responsible for this, I will stand straight without going into this anti-inia wave.

Isn't that all it is!

After the Sirimao era, it is Gotabhaya era that has come to start a production era by putting a stop to the borrowing economy.

It would be in this era if a government acted after Sirimao era to reduce imports and increase exports.

This was the policy the government worked since stopping the imports of yellow and encouraging the country to grow.

Throughout our history, we have said that Sri Lanka is a state surrounded by the sea. But in our country there was never an export market from fish resources.

For the first time in history, the current government created a state ministerial post for it, and created a $500 million export market.

The current government policy was to restrict import everything the country can grow, import only what the country cannot produce.

That is why the President Gotabhaya Rajapaksha worked to form state ministries and hand them over to the young ministers.

The country's annual export revenue was limited to $ two billion throughout history.

Under the current government, the export revenue to this country is a billion dollars monthly.

The result of the export promotion program conducted by that government.

That's why I don't support protests against the government.

The foundation of the struggle is the fuel and gas crisis caused by the dollar crisis.

I don't support this conflict that started decades ago and has been a growing crisis that has started and is not solving by changing the current governance, which is due to the lack of political stability and the crisis is intensifying.

Other countries in the history have faced such crises.

Japan is the best example after World War II. People's lives, consumer patterns have drastically changed due to the economic crisis after the war.

What the Japanese did was not rebellion asking for loan or food.

Working 18 hours a day in factories, working in factories overnight. It is said that Japanese ate bajiri and takola during that time.

Japan was built today because of the great sacrifice and sweat done that day.

I will never ask the people of this country to make sacrifices like Japanese. The people of this country can never do the same.

But I don't support this wave because the unspoken battle lesson of the struggle is "stop everything and get us fed"

Now this struggle has become just a popular wave.

Many involved in the struggle are not perceived of the country's economy crisis, its beginning, broadcast and the current situation.

They think that the president Gotabhaya Rajapaksha has caused an economic crisis in the country, which will cause shortage of fuel gas and power cut.

Ignorance, deceit and popularity will never be achieved. That's why I don't support this struggle.

The answer is learning, awareness and logical thinking.

In the background of this struggle, I saw a news being transfered on Facebook.

It said "There is a way that the loans obtained by dictators of the world history can be taken from themselves, and we (citizens) are not ready to pay the debts that Gotabhaya took."

The hidden truth that the people exchanging these are unknown is that Gotabhaya was the only ruler who did not increase the debt burden of Sri Lanka after 1948.

So far all the rulers have taken more debt than they have paid during their regime.

During this regime of Gotabhaya, he has paid more debt than he took loan. That means getting foreign loans in this country in these two and a half years is a great value.

I don't support this struggle of ignorance, data, hate, anger, misinformation.

Due to the struggle, two countries have already issued tourism risk notifications against Sri Lanka. It's England and America.

Tourism, which has been a major source of revenue that brought dollars to the country in the past few months is collapsing again.

Due to the struggle, the manufacturing process continues to be disrupted in a country amidst a crisis.

It makes the crisis even more fierce and not helping to overcome it.

That's why I don't support this struggle.

I'm well aware of the difficulties when the country has a shortage of gas, and have to spend time in oil polling, and sweat without electricity.

I also know that there is no short term solution to that crisis, and the best thing possible is to solve it through a long term program without inheriting it to another generation.

That's why I don't support this struggle.
